### Can't find worker file?

```bash
# Check what's available
ls -la czarina-{{PROJECT_SLUG}}/workers/
```

### Branch already exists?

```bash
# Check branch status
git branch -a | grep <your-branch-name>

# If it exists and has work, check it out
git checkout <your-branch-name>

# If it doesn't exist, create it
git checkout -b <your-branch-name>
```

### Not sure what to do?

Read your prompt file completely. It has EVERYTHING you need:
```bash
cat czarina-{{PROJECT_SLUG}}/workers/<your-worker-id>.md
```

